<!-- ── ABOUT ── -->
<section id="about">
  <p class="section-label">About</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">A career built in the secondary market</h2>
  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-text">
      <p>
        I'm Curtis Greve — and I've been working in reverse logistics and the secondary market since before most of today's industry platforms existed. I started in Internal Audit at Walmart in 1983, was promoted to head up Walmart's reverse logistics division in 1988. From 1988 to 1993 we saw annual double digit growth, expanded the reverse logistics network to service the continental US and improved productivity by over 150%.
      </p>
      <p>
        From there I spent a decade as President of GENCO, leading return center and liquidation operations for Target, Best Buy, Walmart, Kmart, HP, Dell, and P&amp;G across 123 DCs and Return Centers in North America and Europe. I was part of four acquisitions — through due diligence, negotiations, and full integration.
      </p>
      <p>
        At Inmar Intelligence, I built the largest consumer goods liquidation service in North America from $18M to $92M in annual revenue, eventually overseeing a $100M+ liquidation and remarketing division across 30 facilities. Before launching Curtis Greve Consulting in 2025, I also ran my own liquidation buying and selling operation at MRL NC — buying and selling closeout merchandise into domestic and international secondary markets.
      </p>
      <p>
        I know both sides of the table. I've been the seller trying to maximize recovery and the buyer looking for margin. That dual perspective is what makes my consulting actually useful.
      </p>
      <div class="about-creds">
        <span class="cred-pill">CPA — 1988</span>
        <span class="cred-pill">Harvard Business School Executive Program</span>
        <span class="cred-pill">Wharton Executive Analytics Program</span>
