<!-- ── SERVICES ── -->
<section id="services">
  <div class="section-intro">
    <p class="section-label">Services</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Where I can move the needle for you</h2>
    <p class="section-body">The secondary market is not forgiving to operators who don't know it. Here's where 40 years of experience — and a deep network of buyers and sellers — translates into real results for clients.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="services-grid">

    <div class="service-card featured">
      <div>
        <div class="service-number">Most In-Demand</div>
        <span class="service-tag">Highest ROI</span>
      </div>
      <h3>Liquidation Program Development &amp; Recovery Optimization</h3>
      <p>Most companies are leaving 300–800 basis points on the table. I audit your current liquidation program — grading standards, channel mix, reserve pricing, buyer base, and cycle times — and build a better one. Whether you're running your program in-house or through a third party, I find the leaks and fix them.</p>
      <div class="service-outcome">
        <strong>Typical client result</strong>
        300–800 bps improvement in recovery rate; 20–40% reduction in reverse cycle time
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="service-card">
      <div class="service-number">02</div>
      <h3>Secondary Market Sourcing &amp; Buyer Network Access</h3>
      <p>For liquidators and auction companies looking to source better deals, or retailers and manufacturers looking to sell into a stronger buyer pool — I bring both sides together. My buyer network is the product of 40 years in the market. I help clients source inventory, structure deals, and connect with the right counterparties domestically and internationally.</p>
      <div class="service-outcome">
        <strong>Who this is for</strong>
        Liquidators, auction companies, retailers with volume to move
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="service-card">
      <div class="service-number">03</div>
      <h3>Reverse Logistics Operations &amp; Software Improvement</h3>
      <p>I've built and run reverse logistics operations at scale — from single facilities to 123 DCs across five countries. I help companies diagnose operational inefficiencies in their return centers, select and implement reverse logistics software, and design the processes that separate top-quartile operators from the rest. The right system poorly implemented is just as costly as the wrong system.</p>
      <div class="service-outcome">
        <strong>Deliverables</strong>
        Operations assessment, software RFP &amp; selection, implementation oversight
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="service-card">
      <div class="service-number">04</div>
      <h3>Liquidation RFP Development &amp; Vendor Selection</h3>
      <p>If you're going to market for a liquidation partner, the quality of your RFP determines the quality of your bids — and most companies write terrible RFPs. I've been on both sides: I've responded to hundreds of them as a service provider, and I know exactly what to ask and how to evaluate the responses. I'll help you write the RFP, score the bids, and select the right partner.</p>
      <div class="service-outcome">
        <strong>Why it matters</strong>
        A well-structured RFP typically yields 15–30% higher recovery commitments from bidders
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="service-card">
      <div class="service-number">05</div>
      <h3>M&amp;A Due Diligence — Reverse Logistics &amp; Liquidation</h3>
      <p>Private equity firms and strategic acquirers need someone who has actually run these businesses when evaluating deals in the reverse logistics and liquidation space. I provide operational due diligence — assessing the real value of a target's recovery operations, buyer relationships, and software infrastructure — and advise on post-merger integration of reverse supply chain functions.</p>
      <div class="service-outcome">
        <strong>Track record</strong>
        Participated in 4 acquisitions at GENCO; due diligence through full integration
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="service-card">
      <div class="service-number">06</div>
      <h3>Expert Witness Services</h3>
      <p>When litigation involves reverse logistics operations, liquidation practices, secondary market valuation, or returns management — attorneys and their clients need a credentialed expert who can speak to industry standards with authority. With 40+ years of executive experience and authorship of the industry's leading book, I provide expert testimony, written reports, and consulting support to legal teams on both sides.</p>
      <div class="service-outcome">
        <strong>Case types</strong>
        Contract disputes, insurance claims, business valuations, operational standard-of-care
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── WHO I WORK WITH ── -->
<div id="who">
  <div class="inner">
    <p class="section-label">Who I Help</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Three types of clients. One area of expertise.</h2>
    <p class="section-body">My work is focused entirely on the reverse supply chain and secondary market. Here's who I typically work with and what they're trying to solve.</p>
    <div class="who-grid">
      <div class="who-card">
        <div class="who-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2z"/><polyline points="9 22 9 12 15 12 15 22"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Retailers</h3>
        <p>From regional chains to national omnichannel operators. The problem is usually the same: returns volume is rising, recovery is flat or declining, and no one internally has deep expertise in the secondary market.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Low recovery rates on returns &amp; excess</li>
          <li>Long reverse cycle times tying up cash</li>
          <li>Weak or transactional buyer relationships</li>
          <li>Returns policy costing more than it should</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card">
        <div class="who-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M16 7V5a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Manufacturers</h3>
        <p>Consumer goods manufacturers dealing with returns from retail partners, overstock, end-of-life product, and warranty returns. Most have no real secondary market strategy — they just take whatever a liquidator offers.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>No visibility into secondary market pricing</li>
          <li>Dependent on one or two liquidation relationships</li>
          <li>Vendor return agreements that need renegotiating</li>
          <li>Returns reclamation programs that underperform</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card">
        <div class="who-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 00-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 00-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 003 8v8a2 2 0 001 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 002 0l7-4A2 2 0 0021 16z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Liquidators &amp; Auction Companies</h3>
        <p>Companies that buy and sell secondary market inventory — whether through B2B, auction, export, or bin stores. The issues are sourcing access, recovery modeling, operational efficiency, and building a stable buyer core that doesn't churn.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sourcing deals at the right buy price</li>
          <li>Developing reliable buyer networks</li>
          <li>Improving grading and processing operations</li>
          <li>Growth strategy and business development</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
