<!-- ── SCALE WITH AI ── -->
<section id="ai" style="background:#fff;padding:80px 24px;">
  <div class="inner" style="max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;">
    <p class="section-label">Scale with AI</p>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="max-width:780px;">AI Can Build the Tools Your Liquidation Business Runs On. I Can Show You How to Get Started.</h2>
    <p style="font-style:italic;font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:#444;max-width:740px;margin:0 0 48px;border-left:3px solid #c8873a;padding-left:20px;">
      I'm not a programmer or an AI expert. I'm a 40-year liquidation industry veteran who spent the last year learning these tools as a user — and using them to build real business infrastructure. Buyer databases. Marketing systems. Financial analysis. Sales plans. A website. All of it, without writing a single line of code.
    </p>
    <div style="background:#1a2744;border-radius:8px;padding:36px 40px;margin-bottom:56px;">
      <h3 style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;margin-bottom:14px;">Most Liquidation Buyers Run Lean. AI Lets You Build Infrastructure Without Hiring a Team.</h3>
      <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;color:#cdd5e0;">You're probably doing everything yourself — sourcing, buying, selling, marketing, tracking, planning. The back-office work that should take hours takes days, or doesn't get done at all. AI tools change that equation — once you know how to direct them for this specific business.</p>
    </div>
